<br>
the blade and fist will proc on epic and pretty much any other pet.  I've given them to dire charmed pets, bard charmed, BL, SK and necro pets and they proc on al of them.<br>
<br>
It is evil when the hasted dire charmed giant gets released early and he is hitting you fast and procing a 140DD on you!!<br>
<br>
I don't have epic, so getting the 62 water was my first priority.  The focus items are nice, since I was so used to having them for all my spells it was good to get them upgraded.<br>
<br>
burnout V is nice, not just because it is more haste, but it last 25 minutes vs 15 for all other burnouts!  Thats 4 cast an hour vs 6, and mean a lot less buffing and mana over time.<br>
<br>
The new armor is 6 mana/tic, so thats like finding a FT2 item since our old one was only 4.<br>
<br>
Honestly though, once you get the 62 pet, a proccing weapon for it, and a tank that keeps the pet behind the mob you are doing well.  all the other spells are nice upgrades, but nothing to obsess over.<br>
